    "suggestionContent": "The refreshToken function at lines 77-83 calls `api.post('/auth/refresh', { token })` but has no error handling. If the refresh request fails (expired token, network error, server error), the unhandled promise rejection propagates to the setInterval callback at line 88 which called it. Unhandled rejections in setInterval callbacks are silently swallowed in some environments or crash the process in Node. More critically, if the refresh fails because the token is expired, the user remains logged in with a stale token in state and localStorage. The refreshToken function should catch errors and, on authentication failure (401/403), clear the token and user state to force re-login.",
